        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-12-01T00:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-12-01T00:00:00-05:00" n="509" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d509">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/12–148: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Shanghai</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Cabot</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Shanghai</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-12-01T13:00:00+08:00">December 1, 1948—1 p. m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received December 1—8:15 a. m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2585. Remytel 2449, November 17,<note n="79" xml:id="d509fn79">Not
                        printed.</note> repeated Nanking 1855, Taipei 133. Local Chinese source very
                    intimately connected Madame Wei Tao-ming<note n="80" xml:id="d509fn80">Wife of
                        the Governor of Taiwan.</note> states Taiwan as place of refuge for Chinese
                    untenable as it is anticipated Taiwan uprising will follow disintegration
                    central Government.</p>
                <p>Sent Dept 2585, pouched Nanking 1951, Taipei 138.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Cabot</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
